<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-12T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-12T09:00:00-05:00" n="386" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">725.34/30: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Nicholson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-12T10:00:00-04:00">August 12, 1934—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>36. Department’s telegram No. 31, August 11, 2 p.m. The departure of the
                            Chilean Minister from Asunción has been postponed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Nicholson</hi></signed></closer>
